						<summary>

						<p>Stone setup near the Āñjanēya temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Khara, Jyēshṭha śu. 15.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record was written indifferently. Mentions Vuppa Nāgi Reddi, the headman of the village Kasalūru and Nāpi Reddi, Tingarappa and Ānanttayya. The inscription was engraved by Āpayya.</p>						

						</summary>
